commit.message: version bump

Avoid implicit function declarations in tests, for C99 compatibility (#521)

Include <stdio.h> for printf and define _GNU_SOURCE for execvpe.

Future compilers will not support implicit function declartions by
default, causing these tests to fail to build.

commit.message: version bump
citnames: output writing is an atomic operation
intercept: file writing needs to loop on content until it gets empty

intercept: file open with O_TRUNC to avoid corrupt output if the file is already exists.

If the output of intercept is a file that already exists, the file was not trucated.
Then if the output length is smaller than previous output, the content is corrupt.

documentation: update the man pages about the recent cahnges

Add flag to update old entries flags insted of appending duplicates of them (#497)

* citnames: add parameter for making DuplicateFilter filter duplicates
only by filename

* citnames: use unordered_set for DuplicateFilter

* citnames: Add --update flag

This flag allows to update the output file with new arguments.
It works similarly to the --append flag but instead of replacing and
item only when the filename and the flags match, this flag replaces and
entry when the filename matches

* Add the --update flag to bear

This allows users to enable the --update flag in citnames

* Updated manual to include --update flag

* citnames: Moved --update flag into configuration file

This patch allows to change how --append removes duplicates removing the
entries that match by filename and arguments (old default) or the ones
that match only by filename (new default)

The config option is called 'append_duplicate_mode' and accepts the
values 'file_name_only' and 'all'

* citnames: Rename config value 'append_duplicate_mode' to 'duplicate_filter'

* citnames: Compute and save hashes of entries in DuplicateFilter

This patch improves both performance and memory usage, without storing a
string for each entry

* citnames: Add a derived class for each duplicate detection mode

* citnames: Add a duplicate filter that checks for the input filename and
the output filename

* citnames: cleanup

* citnames: Rename configuration value

Renamed "duplicate_filter" to "duplicate_filter_fields"

* Remove mentions to the --update flag in the man pages

* citnames: Add tests for duplicate_filter_fields + minor cleanup
